.TH SECDAT-FUSE 1 "2026-06-23" "secdat 0.2.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
secdat-fuse \- mount selected secdat keys as read-only files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B secdat-fuse
[\-d DIR|\-\-dir DIR] [\-\-domain DIR] [\-s STORE|\-\-store STORE]
[\-p GLOBPATTERN|\-\-pattern GLOBPATTERN]
[\-x GLOBPATTERN|\-\-pattern-exclude GLOBPATTERN]
[\-\-sandbox-injectable] [\-\-dry-run] [\-f|\-\-foreground] [\-\-debug]
.I MOUNTPOINT
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B secdat-fuse
is an optional FUSE 3 helper built only when
.B secdat
is configured with
.BR \-\-enable-fuse .
It exposes the selected visible keys as read-only files under
.IR MOUNTPOINT .
File reads decrypt values through the public
.B libsecdat
SDK; the helper does not read store internals directly.
.PP
The helper is intentionally read-only. It does not support writes, creates, deletes, renames, chmod, chown, or truncation through the mounted filesystem.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-dir DIR
Set the base directory used for domain resolution.
.TP
.B \-\-domain DIR
Require one exact registered domain root instead of normal ancestor-based discovery.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-store STORE
Select the store namespace inside the resolved domain.
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-pattern GLOBPATTERN
Expose only matching keys. The initial helper accepts one include pattern.
.TP
.B \-x, \-\-pattern-exclude GLOBPATTERN
Exclude matching keys. The initial helper accepts one exclude pattern.
.TP
.B \-\-sandbox-injectable
Expose only keys whose effective sandbox injection policy allows bulk selection.
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Print the mountpoint and selected file names without mounting or reading secret values.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-foreground
Keep the FUSE process in the foreground.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable FUSE debug output.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show usage.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print the secdat-fuse version.
.SH SECURITY
Mounting secrets as files exposes plaintext values through normal file reads. Use a private mountpoint, leave
.B allow_other
disabled, and unmount promptly after the consuming process no longer needs the files. The helper disables kernel caching for the mounted filesystem, but plaintext can still exist transiently in process memory and reader buffers.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
secdat-fuse --dir ~/project --pattern 'APP_*' --dry-run /tmp/secdat-app
secdat-fuse --dir ~/project --pattern 'APP_*' --foreground /tmp/secdat-app
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR secdat (1)
